title: Grateful Dead Live at The Omni on 1990-04-02
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, Mississippi Half Step-> The Weight, Queen Jane Approximately, Easy To Love You, Brown Eyed Women, Let It Grow

Set 2

Foolish Heart, Looks Like Rain, He's Gone, The Last Time, Drums-> Jam-> The Other One-> Death Don't Have No Mercy, Around & Around-> Good Lovin', E: Black Muddy River

reviews.review_text: great show, good recording!  Hey Y'all,  since we are down south !  This is my favorite show of the Atlanta 90 run.  A nice solid performance in both sets with the 2nd set featuring a rare "death don't have no mercy" which is always a cool tune and harbors a very vintage GD vibe from the yesteryear of the Fillmore.  I also like this AUD source,  it's one of my favorites with minimal crowd noise and does have some dynamic range too.  4 stars because the taper included a center mic mix which is always cool in my opinion for recording in large indoor arenas.
